<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-8D15F623-1755-42D9-B2AA-FFAB7EAC28C6" version="1" lang="en-US"?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-8D15F623-1755-42D9-B2AA-FFAB7EAC28C6" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c concept oceConcept-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">11 The function of the <ph varid="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph></title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-34C6A3E5-E809-4139-80CC-275A8CCF9EDC"><p class="- topic/p ">What is the function of the <ph class="- topic/ph " varid="controller">Windows controller</ph> ? 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><section id="GUID-98E1B520-37EF-4919-9F05-51410C4023D2" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Hardware block diagram</title><fig id="GUID-AECADF5B-5874-487F-AB74-DFCD0CA7B019" class="- topic/fig "><title class="- topic/title "/><image href="GUID-7DA8B79E-8A63-4BD3-B62B-59D0B3CE5079-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7DA8B79E-8A63-4BD3-B62B-59D0B3CE5079-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-F5034822-753A-4C8B-A7CD-E44CE7EBD702" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Introduction</title><p class="- topic/p ">The <ph varid="controller" class="- topic/ph ">Windows controller</ph> is an embedded Microsoft Windows 10 Controller 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Below you find the main functions of the controller. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-3225DD38-160F-42B4-A279-10AA00359615" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Network connection and handling</title><p class="- topic/p ">The printer is connected to the customer network through a standard TCP/IP socket connection. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Detailed specifications are: 
</p><table id="GUID-1BC2DB85-D34E-4D58-8932-A7D781974C4E" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" align="left" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Network Setting 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Value 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Interface type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Socket API 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Port Number 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9100 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connections allowed 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Connection speed 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1000 Mbit/s 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The external RIP station establishes a connection through port 9100. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Only one connection to the printer is accepted at any time. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Once the connection has been established, the external RIP station can transfer the print job(s). 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> After sending all the data, the station closes the connection to inform the printer no more data will be sent. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> The printer can print a job while processing or receiving another job 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p ">The external RIP station and the printer communicate using TCP/IP services (DNS, DHCP, …). 
</p></section><section id="GUID-35175714-BD42-4731-A6EF-220A678C5032" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How does the external RIP interface with the printer </title><fig id="GUID-75FE0CA9-934E-46E1-8EFC-509F774CAA1E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-56F69F2E-1109-4B2D-8677-6EBE299CDD52-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-56F69F2E-1109-4B2D-8677-6EBE299CDD52-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The interfaces between the external RIP and the printer are: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> .PRINT</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Mono directional interface used by the external RIP to submit print jobs (bitmaps and settings) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> WebServices</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Bidirectional interface used by the printer to provide information about its status and by the RIP for media management 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Accounting</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Mono directional interface used by the printer to provide accounting information about printed files 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-1070FD93-CFAD-4011-8EAB-1BB9341AD686" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Drive the user panel</title><p class="- topic/p ">Drive the user panel and handle the interaction with the operator. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-17AD9DE0-68AE-4EE1-89FF-539760AEAF25" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Data transport to the <ph varid="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph></title><p class="- topic/p ">The controller transports the job data received from the RIP to the <ph varid="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph>. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The controller sends control information from the user interaction to the <ph varid="Econtroller" class="- topic/ph ">Embedded controller</ph>. 
</p></section></conbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-2F38C42C-05EE-433C-99BD-DEE20037FB92.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</concept>